5:
Look at all these people. Now this is
a festival.
8:
They called it Valentine's—a carnival
of sweets.
12:
What do I do, what do I do, WHAT DO
I DO? We're DOOMED unless some
miracle kid who can handle a sword
AND a ladle comes walking down
this street...
19:
Guys, you have to come with me!
Valentine's—no, all of Palpebra—is
counting on you!
24:
Lilie! Ooh, and you've brought guests
too! Perfect timing!
26:
I've just whipped up my newest
creation! Whooo's ready to be taste
testers?!
30:
Is now really the time, Parfait? What
about getting ingredients?
36:
Yeah, but the thing is, inspiration's
just like lightning. You never know
when or where it's gonna strike! Wait
here. I'll go get plates.
41:
That was Parfait. She's the main
pastry chef for this year's festival.
43:
But she still needs to go out and get
some stuff, and I want you to watch
her.
66:
Uh. No. THAT is Parfait's cooking.
Ladies and gentlemen, kitties and
bunnies, may I introduce you to one
of the world's few...
79:
I'm not gonna argue with that, but I...
I can't believe I just ate giant
tentacles... Urp.
90:
Come on, Lilie. You're overreacting.
They love the flavor.
95:
You know who's gonna be
overreacting? The screaming
crowds when they see this food. Oh,
also the big wigs when they GIVE ME
A DEMOTION!
99: Well, you were the one who hired her.
102:
Yeah, last year, when she was still a
NORMAL PASTRY CHEF. You don't
expect cooks to just start swapping
out icing for eyeballs!
107:
Doesn't fate work in funny ways? It
was right after winning the
nomination, you know.
108:
That's when I discovered the infinite
possibilities of Monster Cuisine!
113:
Would it kill you to feel even a little
sorry? Everyone's so busy prepping
for the festival, I couldn't even find
you a replacement!
117:
Well, it's too late to do anything now.
Don't stress. All it's gonna do is make
you go bald.
121:
Says the CAUSE of my stress.

But yeah, you're right. There's no
time to argue!
123:
Guys! I brought you here for one
reason and one reason only!
126:
You're gonna tail Parfait, and every
time she tries to drop a wriggling
little creature into the mix, you are
gonna protect that batter WITH
YOUR LIFE.
131:
Then we are to be wardens. Are you
all right with that, Parfait?
136: Oh yeah! I love a challenge!
142:
Parfait's a weirdo, but the food she
makes is really good—when there's
no creepy-crawlies in there.
144:
You know what? If she manages to
sneak in a powdered fang or two,
fine. Just make sure everything
LOOKS okay... please?
150:
*sigh* All right, got it. I don't want the
festival ruined either.
160: Well, I'm glad THAT problem's solved.
167:
So, boys and girls, it's time we went
hunting! Cupid's not gonna have
anything on us this Valentine's!
171:
All right. So first, we've gotta collect
cacao fruit. That's gonna form the
base of my creation.
174:
Let us aid you. We will be able to
preserve the dish better if we
understand its ingredients.
178:
I'd love that! Honestly speaking, it is
A LOT of fruit to handle for one
person.
186:
...Has tons of little forest friends!
Keep on your toes!
189:
Well, that cacao ain't gonna pick
itself! I want this whole place swept
clean!
193:
...Maybe I could use that slime for
frosting.
202: This will be a long and hard battle...
